# Atlas Grid MCP

When the user asks about **live application data** (projects, POI, infrastructure, jobs, sand logistics, flow schematics, analysis results), use the **`atlas-grid`** MCP server — not raw `curl`, REST calls, or guessing from code.

## When to use MCP

- Count/list projects, project metadata, POI, infra objects
- Job status, analyze-all, persisted calculation results
- Mutating operations (create POI, update rates, etc.) — **только через веб-чат** (HTTP MCP вернёт `confirm_required`)
- Project cost rates and economic params
- Admin job journal (admin role only)
- Questions like «сколько проектов», «статус задачи», «тарифы», «отмени задачу»

## When NOT to use MCP (`atlas-grid`)

- Reading/editing **source code** in the repo
- Architecture/docs questions answerable from files
- Local **pytest**, **git**, or **code search** — use **`atlas-grid-dev`** stdio MCP instead ([atlas-grid-dev-mcp.mdc](atlas-grid-dev-mcp.mdc))

## Available tools (RBAC-filtered)

Read-only tools (~31): projects, POI, map layers/objects, analysis results, jobs, rates, flow, sand logistics, networks, one-pagers, imports, 3D models, session. **Mutating** (8 tools) заблокированы в HTTP MCP — `confirm_required`; подтверждение в панели AI-помощник. Admin read: `admin_list_jobs`, `admin_jobs_health`, `admin_list_users`, `admin_stats`, `admin_list_assistant_audit`. Полный список: `docs/features/assistant-tools.md` §2.

## Auth

- MCP requires Bearer JWT in `.cursor/mcp.json` (generated locally, gitignored).
- On Windows, `${env:ATLAS_GRID_ACCESS_TOKEN}` in HTTP headers often fails — run `.\scripts\get-atlas-grid-token.ps1` instead (embeds token, ~60 min TTL).
- If MCP returns 401: re-run the script, then reload MCP in Cursor Settings.
- Prod: `https://erascaning.duckdns.org/api/v1/mcp`; local: add `-McpUrl http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/mcp`.

